messages.message:
Hey teamm :slightly_smiling_face: eod update is as follows:
• :white_check_mark: Field extraction and digitization no longer hangs (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C08SC9ZPGFQ/p1757362748440449?thread_ts=1757358736.295599&cid=C08SC9ZPGFQ), as model-service was successfully brought up
• :white_check_mark: Displaying table fields works (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C0976HB6ZPT/p1757350817242159?thread_ts=1757345396.413339&cid=C0976HB6ZPT) for new fields and fields created before the fix just need to be re-ran
• :white_check_mark: Split-classification batch `extraction failed` bug fix merged (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/74412) to master and should land soon
• :loading_wheel: Bug bashing (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C0976HB6ZPT/p1757351644142529) for auto-generate is underway and we'll have a better idea tmrw whether fixes can make it into Wed certify. The investigations are:
    a. split classification is buggy right now with autogeneration due to some schema race conditions. Investigating fixes on both BE and FE
    b. split classification FE intermittently does not display the correct classes tho on reload we see the correct classes. Jaden is currently looking into this
    ◦ minor UI fixes w/ displaying autogenerate option when in legacy mode. Also FE that Jaden will get to
lmk if there's anything I missed, and yep to confirm @margaret.tomaszczuk the GTM is recommended to work more with non-split class cases correct? I remember we made the split-class `extraction failed` bug non-blocking since it was only for split-class, so is the same true for these auto-gen bugs?

hmm i think the first issue in auto gen testing is probably related to that non blocker bug. I'm not seeing extraction failed errors for the whole schema, but seeing all fields being deleted due to race conditions sometimes and also we're not able to save fields in the extracted fields json due to some extra schema requests being made. cc @jaden that it's not a blocker and potentially weiming is working on this.

Thanks @pauline.comising!

Two other items:
• Accuracy runs erroring out (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/AUTO-547) - @pauline.comising do we have an ETA on this one?
• OCR confidence score fix (BE - impacting app runs / human review) (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/AUTO-549) - @Abhishek Adupa 
BG pinged me on these today.
Oo yes, tomorrow I’ll continue looking into the accuracy report one and can give a timeline update then
Thanks Pauline. That one will be critical as evaluation tiger team is comparing accuracy between Legacy and Agent mode as part of evaluation.
OCR confidence issue fix is merged.
Will test once deployed and mark issue done
